 {"id":"bd-a8fzc","title":"add mounted-path btrfs SEEK_DATA/SEEK_HOLE edge-case coverage for fully-allocated and leading-hole files","description":"Survey finding: btrfs mounted-path seek coverage currently proves only the punched-middle-hole scenario, but OpenFs::btrfs_lseek_data/hole also implements fully allocated and leading-hole cases. Scope: add btrfs FUSE probes that freeze SEEK_HOLE on a fully allocated file returning the virtual EOF hole, and SEEK_DATA/SEEK_HOLE on a file with a leading sparse hole returning the next data offset and hole start correctly, including EOF ENXIO behavior. Acceptance: btrfs FUSE E2E covers these sparse-layout edge cases with exact offsets.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:10:59.453875131Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T18:59:55.432979683Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T18:59:55.431125654Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
