+{"id":"bd-aamx0","title":"Align README self-healing claims with detection-only mount scrub","description":"README self-healing deep-dive still says FrankenFS continuously monitors and automatically recovers corrupted data. After bd-4h62v, ffs mount owns a detection-only ScrubDaemon lifecycle and RaptorQ recovery/symbol writes remain explicit ffs repair / ffs fsck --repair operations. Scope: update README wording so automatic recovery claims are limited to explicit repair/fsck paths and mount-time scrub is described as detection-only. Acceptance: README no longer overstates automatic mount-time recovery; docs remain consistent with FEATURE_PARITY mount background scrub lifecycle row.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-29T00:38:50.507240569Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T00:40:16.401915862Z","closed_at":"2026-04-29T00:40:16.400082084Z","close_reason":"Aligned README self-healing wording with detection-only mount scrub and explicit repair/fsck recovery paths","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["docs","mount","repair"]}
